  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2023-03-28",
    "date": "2024-03-11T16:54:43Z",
    "text": "Pandemic Unemployment Fraud Recoupment Act\n\nThis bill extends the time period when a state must recover improperly paid pandemic unemployment insurance (UI) benefits and bring related criminal charges or enforcement actions to 10 years.\n\nThe bill also adds certain recovery requirements to two pandemic UI programs\u2014Pandemic Unemployment Assistance (PUA) and Lost Wages Assistance (LWA)\u2014that match the requirements of other pandemic UI programs. Specifically, the state must (1) repay itself by deducting the PUA or LWA funds from any UI benefits a recipient may later qualify to receive; and (2) ensure the recipient is provided with notice, a hearing, and a final determination."
